<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage">
<h2 class="cliverse-faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
<h3 itemprop="name">What kind of harness is best for a cat?</h3>
<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
<div itemprop="text">
<p>Every cat is different, so there may not be a one-size-fits-all best cat harness. When shopping for a harness, think about your cat’s size, activity level, and comfort to decide on a harness design. Be sure to take your cat’s measurements as well to pick the right size.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
<h3 itemprop="name">Are cat harnesses cruel?</h3>
<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
<div itemprop="text">
<p>There’s nothing cruel about buying your cat a harness, as long as you choose one that fits well and keeps your cat safe. It’s also important to use the harness appropriately – your cat shouldn’t need it unless you’re walking him outdoors.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
<h3 itemprop="name">Can I train my cat to walk on a leash?</h3>
<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
<div itemprop="text">
<p>Yes! Having a cat harness helps keep your cat secure during leash training sessions and the walks that follow. Check out our <a href="https://allaboutcats.com/how-to-walk-a-cat-on-a-leash" target="_blank" rel="noopener">in-depth guide to training a cat</a> to walk on a leash.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
